\[
\begin{align}
5x-8y &= -\frac{64}{16} \\
2x+3y &= \frac{153}{40} \\
\end{align}
\implies
\left[ \begin{array}{cc|c}
5 & -8 & -4 \\
2 & 3 & \frac{153}{40}
\end{array} \right]
\]

Multiplicamos la fila 1 por 1/5

\[
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
5 & -8 & -4 \\
2 & 3 & \frac{153}{40}
\end{array}
\right]
\;\;\xrightarrow{F_1 \to \tfrac{1}{5}F_1}\;\;
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
2 & 3 & \frac{153}{40}
\end{array}
\right]
\]

A la fila 2 le restamos 2 veces la fila 1 \(F_2-2F_1\)

\[
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
2 & 3 & \frac{153}{40}
\end{array}
\right]
\;\;\xrightarrow{F_2-2F_1}\;\;
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
0 & \frac{31}{5} & \frac{217}{40}
\end{array}
\right]
\]

Multiplicamos la fila 2 por su recíproco \(\frac{5}{31}\)

\[
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
0 & \frac{31}{5} & \frac{217}{40}
\end{array}
\right]
\;\;\xrightarrow{F_2 \to \tfrac{5}{31}F_2}\;\;
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
0 & 1 & \frac{7}{8}
\end{array}
\right]
\]

A la fila 1 le restamos \(\frac{8}{5}\) de la fila 2 \(F_1-\frac{8}{5} F_2\)

\[
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & -\tfrac{8}{5} & -\tfrac{4}{5} \\
0 & 1 & \frac{7}{8}
\end{array}
\right]
\;\;\xrightarrow{F_1-\frac{8}{5} F_2}\;\;
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & 0 & \tfrac{3}{5} \\
0 & 1 & \frac{7}{8}
\end{array}
\right]
\]
Solución
\[
\left[
\begin{array}{cc|c}
1 & 0 & \frac{3}{5} \\
0 & 1 & \frac{7}{8}
\end{array}
\right]
\implies
\begin{array}{cc|c}
x=\frac{3}{5} \\
y=\frac{7}{8}
\end{array}
\]

